Create a function that returns true if the number is even and false if the number is odd. The name of the funtion is isEven. In the main function, user will be asked to type an integer and the output will be text Even or Odd.

Tip! You can use modulus (%) operator to check is the numer is odd or even. (n % 2) is 0 if the number is even.


Example output:
Type an integer:
12
Even
The verification of program output is not case-sensitive

//solution

fun main(args: Array<String>) {
	println("Type an integer:")
	val input = readLine()!!.toInt()
	println(isEven(input))
}
fun isEven(input: Int): String{
	if(input%2 == 0) {
		return "Even"
	} else{
		return "Odd"
	}
}
